Additional Commons Clauses – Detailed Descriptions
---------------------------------------------------------------

1. No Commercial Use
   ------------------
   a. Definition: "Commercial Use" is defined as any use of the Software, in whole or in part, that is 
      primarily intended for or directed toward commercial advantage or monetary compensation. This 
      includes, but is not limited to, usage by private individuals, companies, associations, government 
      agencies, or any other entities in any commercial context.
   
   b. Restriction: Under this clause, you are strictly prohibited from using, sublicensing, selling, leasing, 
      or otherwise providing the Software for any commercial purpose. This restriction applies to the 
      Software itself as provided and to any distribution or use from which a substantial economic advantage 
      is derived.
      
   c. Scope: Even if the commercial use is incidental or part of a broader, non-commercial activity, any use 
      intended for commercial benefit or monetary gain is disallowed.

2. Attribution Requirement
   -------------------------
   a. Obligation: Any use, distribution, or publication of the Software, in whole or in part, must include clear 
      and prominent attribution to the original author, "[COPYRIGHT HOLDER]".
      
   b. Format: The attribution must be provided in a manner that is reasonably prominent relative to the medium and 
      the method of distribution. For example, if integrated into a user interface or documentation, the attribution 
      must be visible to end users.
      
   c. Inclusions: The attribution must at a minimum include the name of the original author and a reference to this license. 
      No alteration or removal of the attribution is permitted when redistributing the Software.

3. Prohibition of Re-licensing
   -----------------------------
   a. Principle: Any use, modification, alteration, or creation of derivative works of the Software shall be subject 
      to the conditions of this License. The Software, in its original or modified form, must not be redistributed 
      or made available under any licensing terms different from those set forth herein.
   
   b. No License Amendment: Even if you modify or extend the source code, the Software (including all derivative works) 
      shall remain licensed solely under the terms of this License. You are expressly prohibited from re-licensing the 
      Software, in whole or in part, under any alternative licensing scheme.
   
   c. Enforcement: Any attempt to offer or distribute the Software under licensing terms that differ from those defined 
      herein shall constitute a breach of this License and be rendered null and void.

